{%- comment -%}
  Sales Velocity — PDP / collection social-proof signal.

  Wrapper contract (per docs/tech/studio-liquid-snippets.md "Library Snippets"):
    - variant            : default variant from mo.variants.value.variants
                           variant.content carries the snippet settings.
    - mo                 : spectrum_snippet_instance metaobject drop.
                           Carries `mo.images.value` for the icon_image pool.
    - mutation_handle    : 'mut-{instanceId}' (consumed by wrapper outer div).
    - experience_handle  : (consumed by wrapper outer div).

  Velocity data source: product metafield spectrum.sales_velocity_callout
  (json). Shape per row:
    { targetingTree, saleCount, durationCount, durationUnit }
  durationUnit is 'minutes'|'hours'|'days'|'weeks'|'months'|'all_time'.
  When durationUnit === 'all_time', durationCount may be null/omitted.

  Multiple rows may exist; client-side targeting picks the first match.
  A row with no targetingTree is a catch-all and short-circuits. The
  realistic v1 shape is a single catch-all row.

  SSR renders the first-row-derived copy to avoid empty-DOM flash, but
  ALWAYS leaves data-spectrum-vis="off" on the container. JS flips to
  "on" only after picker + min_count both succeed.

  Sizing uses `em` (not `rem`) — Dawn-family themes set
  `html { font-size: 62.5% }`, which crushes rem-sized chrome.
{%- endcomment -%}

{% stylesheet %}
.sai-vp9q4kxn {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.5em;
  font-family: var(--font-body-family, inherit);
  font-size: 1em;
  color: var(--color-foreground, inherit);
  line-height: 1.4;
}

.sai-vp9q4kxn[data-spectrum-vis="off"] {
  display: none;
}

.sai-vp9q4kxn__icon {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  line-height: 1;
  flex: 0 0 auto;
  font-size: 1.1em;
}

.sai-vp9q4kxn__icon-image {
  display: block;
  width: 1.1em;
  height: 1.1em;
  object-fit: contain;
}

.sai-vp9q4kxn__message {
  font-weight: 500;
}

.sai-vp9q4kxn__count {
  font-weight: 600;
}
{% endstylesheet %}

{%- liquid
  assign settings = variant.content
  assign message_template = settings.message_template | default: '{count} sold in the last {period}'
  assign display_format = settings.display_format | default: 'exact'
  assign icon_emoji = settings.icon_emoji | default: '🔥'

  comment
    Resolve icon_image via the image pool on the snippet instance metaobject.
    variant.content.icon_image carries { kind: "images", refId: "<id>" } when
    set; mo.images.value is the typed pool of resolved image drops. Iterate
    by id-as-string (coerce both sides per generated-liquid rule #4).
  endcomment
  assign icon_image_url = ''
-%}
{%- if settings.icon_image and settings.icon_image.refId and mo.images.value -%}
  {%- assign target_refid = settings.icon_image.refId | append: '' -%}
  {%- for img in mo.images.value -%}
    {%- assign img_id = img.id | append: '' -%}
    {%- if img_id == target_refid -%}
      {%- assign icon_image_url = img.src | default: img.url | default: '' -%}
      {%- break -%}
    {%- endif -%}
  {%- endfor -%}
{%- endif -%}

{%- liquid
  comment
    SSR initial-row resolution. The full rows array is emitted in a JSON
    island below so the JS can apply runtime targeting.
  endcomment
  assign rows_raw = product.metafields.spectrum.sales_velocity_callout.value
  assign initial_row = nil
-%}
{%- if rows_raw != blank -%}
  {%- for row in rows_raw limit: 1 -%}
    {%- assign initial_row = row -%}
  {%- endfor -%}
{%- endif -%}

{%- assign ssr_count_text = '' -%}
{%- assign ssr_period = '' -%}
{%- assign ssr_message_before = '' -%}
{%- assign ssr_message_after = '' -%}
{%- assign ssr_has_message = false -%}

{%- if initial_row != nil -%}
  {%- comment -%}
    SSR count formatter — Liquid lacks locale-aware grouping, so SSR emits
    the raw integer for every display_format. JS replaces this with the
    formatted value on hydrate. Acceptable because vis=off keeps SSR
    hidden until JS runs.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  {%- assign ssr_count_text = initial_row.saleCount | default: 0 -%}

  {%- assign dur_unit = initial_row.durationUnit -%}
  {%- assign dur_count = initial_row.durationCount -%}
  {%- if dur_unit == 'all_time' -%}
    {%- assign ssr_period = 'all time' -%}
  {%- elsif dur_count != nil -%}
    {%- if dur_count == 1 -%}
      {%- assign unit_singular = dur_unit | replace_last: 's', '' -%}
      {%- assign ssr_period = dur_count | append: ' ' | append: unit_singular -%}
    {%- else -%}
      {%- assign ssr_period = dur_count | append: ' ' | append: dur_unit -%}
    {%- endif -%}
  {%- endif -%}

  {%- comment -%}
    Substitute {period} into the template, then split around {count} so
    the count span stays distinct from the surrounding prose — `count`
    is its own style node and merchants style it independently of the
    message wrapper.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  {%- assign tpl_with_period = message_template | replace: '{period}', ssr_period -%}
  {%- assign tpl_parts = tpl_with_period | split: '{count}' -%}
  {%- assign ssr_message_before = tpl_parts | first -%}
  {%- if tpl_parts.size > 1 -%}
    {%- assign ssr_message_after = tpl_parts | last -%}
  {%- endif -%}
  {%- assign ssr_has_message = true -%}
{%- endif -%}

{%- comment -%}
  Velocity callouts island — the full rows array verbatim. Per
  generated-liquid rule #5 the JSON value is emitted through `| json`,
  which both serialises cleanly and escapes any payload chars that
  could break the <script> element (e.g. `</script>` inside string
  values is rewritten to a unicode escape).
{%- endcomment -%}
<script type="application/json" data-spectrum-vp9q4kxn-rows>
{{ product.metafields.spectrum.sales_velocity_callout.value | json }}
</script>

<script type="application/json" data-spectrum-vp9q4kxn-settings>
{
  "message_template": {{ message_template | json }},
  "display_format": {{ display_format | json }},
  "min_count": {{ settings.min_count | json }},
  "icon_emoji": {{ icon_emoji | json }},
  "icon_image_url": {{ icon_image_url | json }}
}
</script>

<div
  class="sai-vp9q4kxn"
  data-spectrum-vis="off"
  aria-live="polite"
  aria-label="Sales velocity information"
>
  <span class="sai-vp9q4kxn__icon" aria-hidden="true">
    {%- if icon_image_url != '' -%}
      <img class="sai-vp9q4kxn__icon-image" src="{{ icon_image_url | escape }}" alt="">
    {%- else -%}
      {{ icon_emoji | escape }}
    {%- endif -%}
  </span>
  <span class="sai-vp9q4kxn__message">
    {%- if ssr_has_message -%}
      {{ ssr_message_before | escape }}<span class="sai-vp9q4kxn__count">{{ ssr_count_text | escape }}</span>{{ ssr_message_after | escape }}
    {%- else -%}
      <span class="sai-vp9q4kxn__count"></span>
    {%- endif -%}
  </span>
</div>

<script src="{{ 'sai-snippet-vp9q4kxn.js' | asset_url }}" defer></script>
